p><p></p><p>He said that, in line with the bank's ethical approach, when a customer switches to it a £25 donation will be made to one of seven leading charities: Action Aid, Amnesty International, the Carers Trust, Help the Hospices, Oxfam, Water Aid, or the Woodland Trust. To qualify, customers must credit their new account with £800 within 31 days.</p><p></p><p>A spokesman said the bank had around 1.6 million current account customers, though in November 2013 it disclosed that it had <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/nov/28/co-op-bank-current-accounts-ethical-paul-flowers\" title=\"\">seen an increase in \"the switching out of current accounts\"</a>. He said the bank was \"the only high street bank with a clear ethical policy based on the views of customers\". Last year, it embedded co-operative values into its constitution, and will consult with customers on the policy in the coming months.</p>","headline":"Co-operative Bank attempts to win back customers with 'golden hello'","trailText":"The bank suffered an increase in 'the switching out of current accounts' folllowing a disastrous 2013 which saw it taken over by US hedge funds","newspaperPageNumber":"24","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3mdj9","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/3/1391444070051/Co-operative-Bank-branch-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/3/1391444070051/Co-operative-Bank-branch-006.jpg","wordcount":"347","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"428811699","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8639737","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Rupert Jones","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-02-04T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2037348","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-06T16:15:44Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":true,"subscriptionDatabases":true},"webUrl"