aper to buy there – an extra 1% isn't going to make a difference and encrouage buyers to move to Wales,\" he said.</p><p></p><p>Nick Barnes, head of research at estate agent Chesterton Humberts, agreed: \"It is likely to benefit first-time buyers, although I suppose it could attract the attention of investors picking up property in big cities such as Swansea and Cardiff where there is a decent-sized population. But it'll be interesting to see if the party actually carry out what they've promised.\"</p><p></p><p>Stamp duty is zero for property sold up to the £125,000 mark; between £125,000 and £250,000 it is 1%; and between £250,000 and £500,000 it is 3%, rising to 4% for properties costing £500,000 to £1m.</p><p></p><p>The Conservatives said they would continue to levy stamp duty at 3% on properties sold for more than £250,000.</p>","headline":"Lowest stamp duty bracket will be axed, say Welsh Conservatives","trailText":"Removal of levy of 1% on homes sold for between £125,000 and £250,000 will help first-time buyers on to ladder, party says","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3mg9y","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391691195901/Houses-in-Denbighshire-no-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391691195901/Houses-in-Denbighshire-no-006.jpg","wordcount":"358","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"429063635","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8652572","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Harriet Meyer","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-02-06T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2039277","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-02-09T13:00:29Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":false,"subscriptionDatabases":false},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2014/feb/06/lowest-stamp-duty-bracket-axed-welsh-conservatives","apiUrl":"http://internal.content