bank.</p><p></p><p>As a result, its financial position is now stronger, but it is in the process of closing 43 branches, plus a further four in Guernsey and the Isle of Man, which will leave it with a total of 250.</p><p></p><p>Steve Britain, commercial director at the bank, said: \"We know we have a lot to do to restore trust in our business, but with our capital position strengthened we are able to begin to talk to customers again about the products and services we can offer them.\"</p><p></p><p>He said that, in line with the bank's ethical approach, when a customer switches to it a £25 donation will be made to one of seven leading charities: Action Aid, Amnesty International, the Carers Trust, Help the Hospices, Oxfam, Water Aid, or the Woodland Trust. To qualify, customers must credit their new account with £800 within 31 days.</p><p></p><p>A spokesman said the bank had around 1.6 million current account customers, though in November 2013 it disclosed that it had <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/nov/28/co-op-bank-current-accounts-ethical-paul-flowers\" title=\"\">seen an increase in \"the switching out of current accounts\"</a>. He said the bank was \"the only high street bank with a clear ethical policy based on the views of customers\". Last year, it embedded co-operative values into its constitution, and will consult with customers on the policy in the coming months.</p>","headline":"Co-operative Bank attempts to win back customers with 'golden hello'","trailText":"The bank suffered an increase in 'the switching out of current accounts' folllowing a disastrous 2013 which saw it taken over by US hedge funds","newspaperPageNumber":"24","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3mdj9","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/3/1391444070051/Co-operative-Bank-branch-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-imag