ed for an afternoon but started again the next day. </strong></p><p></p><p><strong>I have asked my manager to move desks and this may happen in a few months, but I will have to deal with this man in the meantime. Also, if I move someone else will have to put up with him, which seems unfair. A lot of other people have complained about him but my manager just shrugs and says \"There is not much I can do about it\".</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>When it gets particularly loud I have mentioned that I really need to focus, but I get a stupid comment in a stupid voice such as \"You are a woman, you should be able to multi-task\". This man is in his 40s.</strong></p><p></p><p>Do you need advice on a work issue? For Jeremy's and readers' help, send a brief email to <a href=\"mailto:dear.jeremy@theguardian.com\" title=\"dear.jeremy@theguardian.com\">dear.jeremy@theguardian.com</a>. Please note that he is unable to answer questions of a legal nature or reply personally.</p>","headline":"What can I do about a singing colleague who distracts me?","trailText":"<strong>Work advice</strong> He sings the chorus of songs repeatedly, and mutters under his breath and mimics people in silly voices – I can't concentrate","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3ymf7","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Money/Pix/pictures/2014/1/10/1389352744452/Colin-Hunt-the-office-jok-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Money/Pix/pictures/2014/1/10/1389352744452/Colin-Hunt-the-office-jok-006.jpg","wordcount":"354","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"426745526","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8538954","isPremoderated":"false","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-01-10T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2024116","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-01-17T11:20:22Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":true,"subscriptionDatabases":true},"webUrl":"